material.mattext: The sets {1, 2, 3} and {3, 1, 2} are considered equal because sets are unordered.
The set {a, a, b, c} has a cardinality of 4.
The empty set ∅ is a subset of every set.
If A ⊂ B, then A and B can be equal sets.
The symbol x ∈ A means that x is an element of set A.
A set can contain other sets as elements.
The symmetric difference A △ B contains elements that are in both A and B.
The complement of set A (denoted A′) contains all elements from the universal set U that are not in A.
For any two sets A and B, A ∪ B = B ∪ A (union is commutative).
The notation |A| represents the complement of set A.
Which of the following correctly represents "x is not an element of set A"?
Given A = {1, 2, 3} and B = {2, 3, 4}, what is A ∩ B?
What is another notation for the complement of set A besides A′?
If A = {a, b, c} and B = {a, b, c, d, e}, which statement is true?
The set difference A - B (also written A \ B) contains:
What is the cardinality of the empty set ∅?
Given sets A = {1, 2, 3} and B = {3, 4, 5}, what is A ∪ B?
Which symbol represents the symmetric difference of two sets?
For sets A and B, if every element of A is also in B, we write:
Define what makes a collection of elements a "well-defined" set.
Given A = {2, 4, 6} and B = {4, 6, 8}, calculate A △ B (symmetric difference).
If the universal set U = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5} and A = {1, 3, 5}, what is A′?
Write the set {x, x, y, z, z, z} without duplicates and find its cardinality.
Given sets A = {1, 2, 3} and B = {2, 3, 4}, calculate A - B.
List all the subsets, including the empty set, for the set {a, b}.
If A ∩ B = ∅, what is the relationship between sets A and B called?
Given A = {1, 3, 5, 7} and B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}, determine if A ⊂ B, A ⊆ B, or neither. Explain.
Explain why the set {∅} is different from the empty set ∅.
